						<summary>

						<p>Slab lying in a field near the Eṟṟavaṅka.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1466</hi> (wrong for 1469), <hi rend="bold">Plavaṅga, Āshāḍha śu. 11,</hi> corresponding to 1547 A.D., June 28, Tuesday.</p>						

						<p>It registers a gift of land situated between Pedavaḍamānu and Sāvisēṭṭipalle in Kalachapaṭi-sīma, made by <hi rend="italic">Mahānāyaṅkāchārya</hi> Pāpānāyuḍu, son of Vonnam Vōbulnāyuḍu to Subbayyaṁgāru. The sīma was given as <hi rend="italic">nāyankara</hi> to the donor by Nandēla Timmarājayya.</p>						

						</summary>
